2. The Outline Clarifies Structure and Hierarchy
Outline view provides a clear overview of the presentationâ€™s logical framework â€” main points, subpoints, and transitions.
This enhances both the coherence and cognitive accessibility of the message to the audience.
References
VirtualSpeech. (2024). How to Structure Your Presentation, with Examples. Retrieved from https://virtualspeech.com/blog/how-to-structure-your-presentation
SlideModel. (2023). Presentation Structure Guidelines for Effective Communication. Retrieved from https://slidemodel.com/presentation-structure
